# Trivy ignore file for Mental Health Days e-commerce infrastructure
# https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore
#
# Format: <avd-id> [exp:<expiry-date>] [<namespace>] # <comment>
# All accepted risks are documented with justification.
# Review this file periodically and remove suppressions that are no longer valid.

# AVD-AWS-0176: DynamoDB table not encrypted with Customer Managed Key (CMK)
# Justification: DynamoDB tables use AWS-managed AES-256 encryption which meets
# the encryption-at-rest requirement for this project. CMK adds operational
# overhead without proportionate benefit at current scale. The optional
# kms_key_arn variable is available in the database module for future use.
AVD-AWS-0176

# AVD-AWS-0017: CloudWatch log group not encrypted with KMS
# Justification: Operational logs (API Gateway access logs) do not contain
# sensitive user PII. The api module exposes an optional kms_key_arn variable.
# Revisit if logs are expanded to include PII or if compliance requirements
# mandate CMK encryption.
AVD-AWS-0017

# AVD-AWS-0090: S3 bucket does not have event notifications configured
# Justification: S3 buckets serve static website content and access logs.
# Event notifications are not required for this CDN-delivery pattern.
AVD-AWS-0090

# AVD-AWS-0010: S3 bucket does not have cross-region replication enabled
# Justification: Static website assets are source-controlled in Git.
# CloudFront's global edge network provides the required availability.
# Cross-region replication adds cost without proportionate DR benefit.
AVD-AWS-0010

# AVD-AWS-0031: CloudFront distribution does not have a Web Application Firewall
# Note: WAF is controlled by the enable_waf variable and is enabled in production.
# This suppression applies only to the www/redirect distribution where WAF is
# intentionally disabled to reduce cost (the primary distribution has WAF enabled).
AVD-AWS-0031

# AVD-AWS-0071: CloudFront distribution does not have geo-restriction enabled
# Justification: Global access is required for a mental health advocacy and
# e-commerce site. Geo-blocking would prevent access for users in regions with
# the greatest need for mental health resources.
AVD-AWS-0071

# AVD-AWS-0051: CloudFront origin does not have failover configured
# Justification: Single-origin architecture is appropriate for static website
# hosting. CloudFront's own infrastructure provides availability guarantees.
# Origin failover requires a secondary origin, which is not applicable here.
AVD-AWS-0051
